            <div id="dsq-comment-message-153501" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>Okay, I&#8217;m confused now. See, I quite like the idea of taxing land, because it taxes wealth rather than income. But isn&#8217;t the whole point of Bitcoin (or rather, one of its functions you&#8217;re in favour of &#8211; genuine question; maybe I&#8217;ve misunderstood your position) that it allows you to shield your wealth from the state? So why is it better to tax land wealth than Bitcoin wealth?</p>
<p>Or, to put it another way, if I was fabulously wealthy, what&#8217;s to stop me from selling my land, renting it back (or living in a hotel) and putting all my wealth into Bitcoins which the state can&#8217;t touch?</p>
