<p>This brings up an interesting correlation: there is a relationship between the value of a bitcoin and the cost of the silicon and electricity which is used to exploit them (not just mine them but to use them too) there&#8217;s a sort of bobbling transform of memory bits and cpu flops that spells out an informationaly  fundamental value scale.</p>
